{"build_type":"library","description":"Thread-local global access codegen (de-globalization, step 4 generalization). For a gload/gstore, looks up the target global's FS-block offset via resolve-thread-local-slot-offset-by-global-name (tls_probe_slot->0, tls_cursor->8, tls_end->16; 999=not thread-local). If thread-local, emits an FS-segment-relative access at that offset (mov rax, fs:[off] / mov fs:[off], rax) so each thread reads/writes its own copy via the FS base, and returns 1. Otherwise returns 0 so the normal shared-global codegen handles it. The real arena migration extends the offset registry with the arena globals.","module_name":"encode-thread-local-global-access-inside-instructions","package_name":"encode-thread-local-global-access-inside-instructions","function_definitions":{"encode-thread-local-global-access-inside-instructions":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"inst","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"code","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"slotmap","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"fixups","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sentinel","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":999},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_it","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"instruction_type"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_dest","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"dest"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_target","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"targe